author: Yining  Shi
text:
Hi Yang,  Thank you for taking the time to interview me in ITP. I had a great time talking to you. I would be very happy to have a chance to work at your team.  Last week, I had an interview with Martin. We talked about the question you asked me in ITP("If you can do anything at apple website, what would you do?"). The conversation is interesting, so I wanted to share it with you:  I said, "if the people are using iOS device to visit the apple website, the apple website can sign users in automatically, in this way apple website can deliver personalized experiences to people by changing some parts of the content. If the user is health conscious, the website will recommend more things about sports app." Then Martin talked about the privacy issue raised by this design. And I said perhaps we could ask people for permission of sharing their data.  In addition, I did a web development project which is a RESTful web interface designed to work with a physical LED alarm. I documented it in my portfolio: http://1023.io/
                          led-alarm/. Feel free to take a look at it.
                          
                           Please let me know if you have any questions for me. Looking forward to hear from you.
                          
                           thanks,
                           Yininghttp://1023.io/

text:
Hi Martin,  Thank you for taking the time to interview me last week. I had a great time talking to you. I would be very happy to have a chance to work at your team.   I feel the very same way when you talked about people who are interested in both design and coding. After you said your teams' work is to combine the beautiful design and advanced technology, I became more and more interested in this position.  Like I mentioned during the interview, I did a web development project which is a RESTful web interface designed to work with a physical LED alarm. I documented it in my portfolio: http://1023.io/
